	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f98604996289658>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Crusader's and Darkforge</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Mar 31st 9:46 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17100><span id=Sage>sleepybri</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>38 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.85]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I would like to clear up some confusion that has been going around for anyone that is starting their Darkforge Quest.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>1.) Crusader's DO have pets.  In the past this wasn't true, but Verant has added this, so if someone tells you that they don't, correct them.<br>(Stupid pets, accidently dropped a HT on it, and not his master)<br><br>2.)Our low lvl spell Sense the Dead WILL point you in the direction of the nearest crusader pet in Cazic-Thule.  Now actually getting to that point is a different story, but at least it will tell you that a crusader is up and the general direction.<br><br>3.) Crusader's are SK's around 33-35, so they have every spell that we have.  Some might say that all they have is HT, but that again might have been changed (not sure).  But I do know that they have all our spells (Darkness, Fear, Lifetap) its just the matter of getting these spells to stick (usually resisted)<br><br>This is a long and painful quest, so help the other SK's in the zone out.  Talk to each other to see what pieces everyone needs, and by all mean don't announce in /ooc that there is extra decayed.  Nothing pisses me off more than some Druid running over and looting some decayed and a SK getting there after him to get a "sorry, someone else got here first" Good Luck to all that are starting their journey down this long road.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
