	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=6567><span id= >Nitsujlak</span></a><br><span id=notbold>176 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.31]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>good post Sleepybri... this made me think of my post a while back about DF armor... thought i'd repost it since a lot of people liked it. With these two guides SK's are sure to be getting that darkforge =)<br><br><br>--------------------------------------------------I have no clue about the sense heading thing, BUT i do know some lil hints about these lil buggers. I have hunted in cazic since level 23-34 (off and on) and seen lots of crusaders. Unless you are really high level its best to get in a group with at least one healer and one enchanter (bard ok if you cant get a chanter). I found the best thing to do is a get a well built, brave, group and take them to Lower throne room. Clear out the lower throne room, then pull from the upper throne room. This is where the crusader spawns. It placeholder is the Lizard Zealot. Now since the group is still in lower throne room you have to stop pulling from upper when the weak lizards outside start repopping. That means that the harder ones inside the throne room are about to pop. If you havent figured it out yet Lower/upper throne room is my favorite place for decaying. One night i didnt get any all night, then right before i was about to log one spawned my group pulled it, and then just a few minutes later another spawned AND THEN ANOTHER! so its really sporatic, but you can do it. Oh yah and one more thing.... the Crusaders always start out a fight with HARM TOUCH. So what my group would do is use one guy as bait, get harm touched, then he sits and heals while the others go in for the kill. This gives time to the healers to heal everyone. <br>Of course if you are good at controlling that pet you can always summon a skeleton and let him take that HT.<br><br>Please rate this post at will =) <br>Nitsujlak Barshemguud Ogre Shm <br>Blackendheart Darkendsoul Ogre Shadowknight <br>both on prexus<br> both in "Legacy"<br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
